      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the immense pain in your thought that you feel like a burden, but it is important to gently remind you that your daughter is not leaving you because she cannot love you, but because she is already struggling to hold on right now. While it sounds like letting go would bring her peace, that is not the reality of how much she already loves you and wants to support you. Please consider speaking with a therapist or counselor, as these feelings of being a weight are a sign of deep depression that can be treated, and they will not be able to help you if you feel alone in them.",
